name: middesk
label: Middesk
description: Middesk is an identity platform that automates business verification and underwrites decisions. It also provides data on businesses and notifies service providers of changes to its customer base allowing them to form an accurate picture of their customers and offer the critical products their customers need to establish,operate, and maintain their businesses.

fields.title: Get Access Token
options: OAuth Access Token - on behalf of account owners
fields.name: auth_type
fields.description: Select the method using which you will get authenticated to access the Middesk APIs. You can choose between API keys or OAuth access tokens - on behalf of account owners. For more information, see the Getting Access Code section.

API Key.title: API Key
API Key.name: token
API Key.description: Specify the Middesk API Key through which you will connect and perform actions on Middesk.
API Key.tooltip: Specify the Middesk API Key through which you will connect and perform actions on Middesk.

OAuth Access Token - on behalf of accoun.title: Client ID
OAuth Access Token - on behalf of accoun.name: client_id
OAuth Access Token - on behalf of accoun.description: Unique ID of the Middesk that is used to create an authentication token required to access the API. Located on the https://app.middesk.com/settings/credentials.
OAuth Access Token - on behalf of accoun.tooltip: Unique ID of the Middesk that is used to create an authentication token required to access the API.

OAuth Access Token - on behalf of accoun.title: Client Secret
OAuth Access Token - on behalf of accoun.name: client_secret
OAuth Access Token - on behalf of accoun.description: Unique Client Secret of the Middesk that is used to create an authentication token required to access the API. Located on the https://app.middesk.com/settings/credentials
OAuth Access Token - on behalf of accoun.tooltip: Unique Client Secret of the Middesk that is used to create an authentication token required to access the API.

OAuth Access Token - on behalf of accoun.title: Authorization Code
OAuth Access Token - on behalf of accoun.name: code
OAuth Access Token - on behalf of accoun.tooltip: The authorization code that you acquired in the authorization step.
OAuth Access Token - on behalf of accoun.description: The authorization code that you acquired during the authorization step. For more information, see Getting Access Code section. using the OAuth Access Token - on behalf of account owners

OAuth Access Token - on behalf of accoun.title: Redirect URI
OAuth Access Token - on behalf of accoun.name: redirect_uri
OAuth Access Token - on behalf of accoun.tooltip: The redirect_uri which you have provided while generating the Access Code
OAuth Access Token - on behalf of accoun.description: The redirect_uri which you have provided while generating the Access Code.

fields.title: Verify SSL
fields.name: verify_ssl
fields.description: Specifies whether the SSL certificate for the server is to be verified or not. By default, this option is set as True.

operations.title: Create Business
operations.description: Creates a new Business for verification and due diligence. Once created, Middesk will automatically begin the process of verifying the legitimacy of this Business and evaluating a number of other risk signals about this Business entity.

parameters.title: Name
parameters.description: Specify the legal entity name of a Business
parameters.name: name
parameters.tooltip: Specify the legal entity name of a Business

parameters.title: Tax Identification Number
parameters.description: Specify the business' tax identification number
parameters.name: tin
parameters.tooltip: Specify the business' tax identification number

parameters.title: Website
parameters.description: Specify the business website
parameters.name: website
parameters.tooltip: Specify the business website

parameters.title: Phone Numbers
parameters.description: Specify the phone numbers. You can specify multiple phone numbers as comma-separated values.
parameters.name: phone_numbers
parameters.tooltip: Specify the phone numbers. You can specify multiple phone numbers as comma-separated values.

parameters.title: External ID
parameters.description: Specify the custom field identifier for system outside Middesk
parameters.name: external_id
parameters.tooltip: Specify the custom field identifier for system outside Middesk

parameters.title: Orders
parameters.description: Specify the orders for the types of products you would like Middesk to fulfill for the business you're submitting.You can specify multiple orders as comma-separated values.For more details (https://docs.middesk.com/reference/order). Valid values are identity, tin, documents, and liens.
parameters.name: orders
parameters.tooltip: Specify the orders for the types of products you would like Middesk to fulfill for the business you're submitting.You can specify multiple orders as comma-separated values.For more details (https://docs.middesk.com/reference/order). Valid values are identity, tin, documents, and liens.

parameters.title: Tags
parameters.description: Specify the tags. You can specify multiple tags as comma-separated values. Any tag can be added (Note that low_priority is a reserved tag, and will affect business turnaround time).
parameters.name: tags
parameters.tooltip: Specify the tags. You can specify multiple tags as comma-separated values. Any tag can be added (Note that low_priority is a reserved tag, and will affect business turnaround time).

parameters.title: Formation
parameters.description: Specify the business formation (Two-Letter abbreviation for the state the business was formed in)
parameters.name: formation
parameters.tooltip: Specify the business formation (Two-Letter abbreviation for the state the business was formed in)

parameters.title: Names
parameters.description: Specify a list of entity names of the business (Doing Business As names supported here)
parameters.name: names

parameters.title: Addresses
parameters.description: Specify the list of addresses (places of business)
parameters.name: addresses

parameters.title: People
parameters.description: Specify a list of people associated with the business
parameters.name: people
parameters.tooltip:
Specify a list of people associated with the business e.g: [
        {
            "name": "Kyle Mack",
            "first_name": "Kyle",
            "last_name": "Kyle",
            "dob": "YYYY/MM/DD",
            "ssn": "abc",
            "address_line1": "577 howard street",
            "address_line2": "suite 400",
            "city": "san francisco",
            "state": "CA",
            "postal_code": "94105",
            "phone_number": "6507970487",
            "email": "abc@xyz.com",
            "device_session_id": "abc"
        }
    ] Note name is a mandatory field

operations.title: Get Businesses List
operations.description: Retrieves the details of all Businesses that have run through Middesk.

parameters.title: Offset
parameters.description: Specify the page offset at which you'd like to resume fetching Businesses
parameters.name: page
parameters.tooltip: Specify the page offset at which you'd like to resume fetching Businesses.

parameters.title: Limit
parameters.description: Specify the number of Businesses to fetch. Default is 25 Maximum is 30.
parameters.name: per_page
parameters.tooltip: Specify the number of Businesses to fetch. Default is 25 Maximum is 30.

operations.title: Get Business
operations.description: Retrieves the details of an existing business based on the id of a Business you have provided
